# Mini Feedback App

A small full-stack application that allows users to submit feedback and view all submitted feedbacks.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Features

Frontend (React):

Feedback form to submit feedback.

List of submitted feedbacks displayed below the form.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Backend (Django):

REST API to store and retrieve feedback.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Data storage:

If MongoDB is available, feedback is stored in MongoDB.

feedback is stored in a JSON file inside the server folder.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tech Stack

Frontend: React (Vite)

Backend: Python Django + Django REST Framework

Database: MongoDB and JSON file 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Setup Instructions

# Backend Setup

# Clone the repository:

git clone <your-repo-url>
cd server
----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Create a virtual environment and activate it:

python -m venv .venv
# Windows
.venv\Scripts\activate


-----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Install backend dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Run migrations:

python manage.py migrate

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Start the backend server:

python manage.py runserver


The backend API will be available at http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Frontend Setup

Navigate to the frontend folder:

cd client/feedback-frontend/

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Install dependencies:

npm install

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Start the frontend development server:

npm run dev


The frontend will be available at http://localhost:5173/ (or the port Vite shows).
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Usage

Open the frontend in a browser.

Fill in the feedback form and submit.

Submitted feedbacks appear below the form in a list.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notes

Data storage:

If MongoDB is connected, feedbacks are stored in MongoDB.

Otherwise, feedbacks are saved in a JSON file inside the server folder.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
